{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770127074,"nonce":"oxfAzBK8Yo+PUE1Njwc29YmIeXM=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87n8kFp","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/137","origin":"github"},"title":"Enhance Status Check with Sync and GitHub Integration","message":"# Plan: Enhance Status Check with Sync and GitHub Integration\n\n## Problem Statement\nThe current `status_report.sh` script provides repository status but doesn't:\n1. Sync repositories before checking status (stale information)\n2. Show open PRs across the workspace\n3. Show open issues across repositories\n\nUsers need a comprehensive status view that includes both local git state and GitHub PR/issue tracking.\n\n## Proposed Solution\nCreate a NEW enhanced status script (`.agent/scripts/status_full.sh`) that:\n1. **Sync first**: Fetch latest changes from all repositories before reporting status\n2. **Add PR tracking**: Query GitHub API for open PRs across all workspace repositories\n3. **Add issue summary**: Show count of open issues per repository\n4. **Format PRs as table**: Display PRs with clickable GitHub links\n5. **Add CLI flags**: Support `--skip-sync` and `--skip-github` options\n6. **Preserve existing**: Keep current `status_report.sh` unchanged for compatibility\n\n## Implementation Tasks\n\n### Task 1: Add Repository Sync Step\n- [ ] Add pre-check sync phase that fetches (not pulls) latest from all repositories\n- [ ] Use `vcs custom --git --args fetch --quiet` for workspace layers\n- [ ] Use `git fetch --quiet` for root repository\n- [ ] Show sync progress with status indicators (✅/⚠️)\n- [ ] Handle failures gracefully (don't abort on sync errors)\n- [ ] Respect `--skip-sync` flag to skip this step entirely\n- [ ] Preserve worktree detection logic from existing script\n\n### Task 2: Add GitHub PR Tracking\n- [ ] Query GitHub API for open PRs using `gh` CLI\n- [ ] Iterate through all repositories (root + overlay repos from `list_overlay_repos.py`)\n- [ ] Create markdown table with columns: Repository, PR, Title\n- [ ] Make PR # clickable link (format: `[#34](https://github.com/owner/repo/pull/34)`)\n- [ ] Truncate titles longer than 80 characters\n- [ ] Show total PR count summary at end\n- [ ] Show \"No open pull requests\" message if none found\n- [ ] Respect `--skip-github` flag to skip this step\n\n### Task 3: Add GitHub Issue Summary\n- [ ] Query GitHub API for open issue counts per repository\n- [ ] Create summary table showing repository name and issue count\n- [ ] Make repository names clickable links to GitHub issue pages\n- [ ] Show total issue count across workspace\n- [ ] Only show repositories that have open issues (reduce noise)\n- [ ] Handle rate limit errors gracefully (show partial data)\n- [ ] Respect `--skip-github` flag to skip this step\n\n### Task 4: Script Organization \u0026 Structure\n- [ ] Create new file: `.agent/scripts/status_full.sh`\n- [ ] Add argument parsing for `--skip-sync` and `--skip-github` flags\n- [ ] Organize output into clear sections:\n  - Section 1: Repository Sync (if not skipped)\n  - Section 2: Repository Status (reuse existing logic)\n  - Section 3: GitHub PRs (if not skipped)\n  - Section 4: GitHub Issues (if not skipped)\n- [ ] Add horizontal dividers (`---`) between sections for readability\n- [ ] Add section headers with step numbers\n\n### Task 5: Error Handling \u0026 Dependencies\n- [ ] Check if `gh` CLI is available, show helpful message if not\n- [ ] Handle GitHub API rate limits gracefully\n- [ ] Handle private/inaccessible repositories\n- [ ] Add timeout protection for slow network calls\n- [ ] Preserve existing functionality if GitHub queries fail\n\n### Task 6: Documentation\n- [ ] Add comprehensive script header comments with usage examples\n- [ ] Document flags: `--skip-sync`, `--skip-github`, `--help`\n- [ ] Add to `.agent/AI_CLI_QUICKSTART.md` under \"Quick Command Reference\"\n- [ ] Add to root `README.md` if appropriate\n- [ ] Document `gh` CLI as optional dependency\n- [ ] Add note about GitHub authentication (`gh auth login`)\n- [ ] Document expected output format in comments\n\n### Task 7: Makefile Integration\n- [ ] Add new target to `Makefile`: `status-full`\n- [ ] Wire up to call `.agent/scripts/status_full.sh`\n- [ ] Keep existing `status` target unchanged (backward compatibility)\n- [ ] Add `status-full` to Makefile help output\n- [ ] Document the difference between `make status` and `make status-full`\n\n### Task 8: Testing \u0026 Validation\n- [ ] Test with all repositories clean (happy path)\n- [ ] Test with uncommitted changes in some repos\n- [ ] Test with no open PRs or issues\n- [ ] Test with `gh` CLI not installed (graceful degradation)\n- [ ] Test with `--skip-sync` flag\n- [ ] Test with `--skip-github` flag\n- [ ] Test in worktree context (verify worktree detection works)\n- [ ] Test offline mode (no network access)\n- [ ] Verify existing `make status` still works unchanged\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- ✅ New script created: `.agent/scripts/status_full.sh`\n- ✅ Script fetches (not pulls) all repositories before status check\n- ✅ Open PRs displayed in markdown table with clickable GitHub links\n- ✅ Issue counts shown per repository with clickable links\n- ✅ Script works offline (degrades gracefully without `gh` CLI)\n- ✅ `--skip-sync` and `--skip-github` flags work correctly\n- ✅ Existing `status_report.sh` and `make status` unchanged\n- ✅ New Makefile target `make status-full` added\n- ✅ Clear visual sections separate sync, status, PRs, and issues\n- ✅ Total counts shown for PRs and issues\n- ✅ Worktree detection preserved from original script\n- ✅ All test scenarios pass\n\n## Technical Considerations\n\n### Dependencies\n- **Required**: `vcs` (vcstool), `git`, `python3`, `jq`\n- **Optional**: `gh` (GitHub CLI) - for PR/issue tracking\n\n### Script Location\n- **New script**: `.agent/scripts/status_full.sh`\n- **Keep existing**: `.agent/scripts/status_report.sh` (unchanged)\n- **Rationale**: Avoid breaking existing workflows that depend on current output format\n\n### GitHub API Access\n- Use `gh` CLI for authenticated GitHub API access\n- Parse JSON output with `jq`\n- Repos come from `list_overlay_repos.py` output\n\n### Performance\n- Fetch step may take 30-60 seconds for all workspaces (6 layers × 21 repos)\n- GitHub queries may take 5-10 seconds (~42 API calls for PRs + issues)\n- `--skip-sync` flag reduces runtime to ~10-15 seconds\n- `--skip-github` flag reduces runtime to ~5 seconds (offline mode)\n- Combined flags give equivalent performance to current `status_report.sh`\n\n### Command-Line Interface\n```bash\nstatus_full.sh [OPTIONS]\n\nOPTIONS:\n  --skip-sync      Skip repository fetch step (faster, may show stale data)\n  --skip-github    Skip GitHub PR/issue queries (offline mode)\n  --help           Show usage information\n\nEXAMPLES:\n  status_full.sh                    # Full status with sync and GitHub\n  status_full.sh --skip-sync        # Quick check without network fetch\n  status_full.sh --skip-github      # Local status only (offline)\n```\n\n## Design Decisions\n\n### 1. New Script vs Modify Existing\n**Decision**: Create new script `.agent/scripts/status_full.sh`\n**Rationale**: Preserves backward compatibility; existing scripts/workflows won't break\n\n### 2. Sync Strategy: Fetch vs Pull\n**Decision**: Use `git fetch` (not `git pull`)\n**Rationale**: Safer - won't modify working tree or fail on local changes; just updates remote tracking\n\n### 3. PR Table Format\n**Decision**: Clickable PR # (e.g., `[#34](url)`), truncated title\n**Rationale**: Keeps table compact while providing direct links\n\n### 4. Issue Display\n**Decision**: Show count only, not individual issues\n**Rationale**: 50+ issues across repos would be too verbose; counts with links are sufficient\n\n### 5. Caching GitHub Data\n**Decision**: No caching in initial implementation\n**Rationale**: Script runs infrequently; caching adds complexity; can add later if needed\n\n### 6. Default Behavior\n**Decision**: Sync and GitHub queries enabled by default\n**Rationale**: Users expect fresh data; flags allow opting out for speed\n\n## Effort Estimate\n**Medium** (6-8 hours)\n- Task 1 (Sync): 1 hour\n- Task 2 (PR Tracking): 1.5 hours\n- Task 3 (Issue Summary): 1 hour\n- Task 4 (Script Organization): 1 hour\n- Task 5 (Error Handling): 1 hour\n- Task 6 (Documentation): 0.5 hours\n- Task 7 (Makefile Integration): 0.5 hours\n- Task 8 (Testing): 1.5 hours\n\n## Related Files\n- `.agent/scripts/status_report.sh` - Current status script (reference implementation)\n- `.agent/scripts/status_full.sh` - NEW script to create\n- `.agent/scripts/list_overlay_repos.py` - Repository discovery\n- `.agent/scripts/lib/workspace.py` - Workspace utilities\n- `Makefile` - Entry point for `make status` and `make status-full`\n- `.agent/AI_CLI_QUICKSTART.md` - Documentation to update\n\n## Example Output Format\n\n```markdown\n# Enhanced Workspace Status Report\n**Date**: Mon Feb 3 08:50:15 EST 2026\n\n## Step 1: Syncing Repositories\n\nSyncing root repository... ✅\nSyncing core workspace... ✅\nSyncing platforms workspace... ✅\n...\n\n---\n\n## Step 2: Repository Status\n\n### Root Repository\n- **Status**: ✅ Clean\n- **Branch**: main\n\n### Workspace: core (Total: 5, Clean: 4, Attention: 1)\n...\n\n---\n\n## Step 3: GitHub Pull Requests\n\n| Repository | PR | Title |\n|------------|-----|-------|\n| unh_marine_autonomy | [#34](url) | Add test infrastructure for automated testing |\n\n**Total Open PRs**: 1\n\n---\n\n## Step 4: GitHub Issues\n\n| Repository | Open Issues |\n|------------|-------------|\n| [ros2_agent_workspace](url) | 14 |\n| [unh_marine_autonomy](url) | 13 |\n| [camp](url) | 8 |\n...\n\n**Total Open Issues**: 56\n\n---\n\n✅ **Status report complete**\n```","files":null}]}